    "The model's performance reflects its training data, meaning that existing biases in the literature could be perpetuated or amplified in its reviews.",
    "Addressing these challenges requires a concerted effort to ensure that training datasets are diverse, representative, and regularly updated to reflect evolving scholarly perspectives.",
    "Furthermore, transparent reporting of the model's methodologies, limitations, and decision-making processes is essential to foster trust and reliability.",
    "Developing ethical guidelines and oversight mechanisms for AI-assisted research will be crucial in ensuring that these tools serve to enhance the integrity and inclusivity of academic discourse.",
    "ConclusionThis study has performed a careful examination of the capabilities of Mistral Large Language Model (LLM), augmented with Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), in conducting automatic literature reviews, and compared its performance against traditional human review processes."
